title.narrative: Output 2: By the end of 2019, health facilities and communities in Mali have knowledge and capacities for the treatment of Severe Acute Malnutrition (SAM)

description.narrative: In 2019, no health district experienced a stockout of RUTF and 76 per cent of the expected 190,000 SAM cases enrolled in the treatment program and 90.3 per cent fully recovered, 0.8 per cent died, 7.3 per cent dropped out of treatment, and 0.7 per cent did not recover, in compliance with global standards. A key achievement was the further decentralization of SAM treatment to community health workers sites, where 10 per cent of all admitted SAM cases were managed. | Status:Met | As-of Date:07/02/2020
